# WAL Storage Engine

A fault-tolerant **Write-Ahead Logging (WAL) Storage Engine** built in modern **C++23** for durable event persistence, binary logging, crash recovery, and asynchronous metadata indexing.

The engine implements append-only binary logging, SQLite-based metadata indexing, deterministic recovery through WAL replay, and a Python monitoring dashboard for real-time storage analytics.

---

# Features

## Storage Engine

- Append-only binary Write-Ahead Logging
- Sequential disk persistence
- Packed binary transaction serialization
- Batched in-memory buffering
- Background log flushing

## Recovery

- WAL replay
- Deterministic crash recovery
- State reconstruction
- Binary log parsing

## Metadata Indexing

- SQLite integration
- Transaction indexing
- File offset tracking
- Volume analytics

## Monitoring Dashboard

- Transaction analytics
- Indexed records
- WAL size monitoring
- Recovery execution
- Storage metrics

---

# Architecture

```text
                Client Transactions
                        │
                        ▼
                WAL Storage Engine
                        │
                In-Memory Buffer
                        │
               Background Flush
                        │
                        ▼
             Append-Only Binary WAL
                        │
          ┌─────────────┴─────────────┐
          ▼                           ▼
    Recovery Engine          SQLite Metadata
                 └───────────┬───────────┘
                             ▼
                 Python Dashboard
```

